Mauritian Mobile-Phone Charges to Decline by at Least 25%, le Defi Reports

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-05-02T09:33:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-02/mauritian-mobile-phone-charges-to-decline-by-25-defi-reports.html
Mauritian mobile-phone charges will be
reduced by a minimum of 25 percent, le Defi reported, citing
Telecommunications Minister Tassarajen Chedumbrum Pillay.  The ministry asked the Information and Communication
Technologies Authority to review prices, the Port Louis-based
newspaper said on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story: Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port
Louis via Johannesburg at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  